<tr><td><div>

<font size="+4" color=#990000>A few stem-changing verbs</font> go from <font color="#0A14C4"><strong>e</strong></font> 
to <font color="#0A14C4"><strong>i</strong></font>.<br>

<table align="center" cellpadding=10" bgcolor="#D7EBD7" width="100%" border=1>
<tr><td colspan=2 align=center><div><strong>Pedir (the "<font color="#0A14C4">e</font>" in the stem turns into 
"<font color="#0A14C4">i</font>")</strong></div></td></tr>
<tr>
<td valign="bottom" bgcolor=#FFAFAF><div>yo p<font color="#0A14C4"><strong>i</strong></font>do</div></td>

<td valign="bottom"><div>nosotros / nosotras pedimos</div></td></tr>
<tr>
<td valign="bottom" bgcolor=#FFAFAF><div>t&uacute; p<font color="#0A14C4"><strong>i</strong></font>des</div></td>

<td valign="bottom"><div>vosotros / vosotras ped&iacute;s</div></td></tr>

<tr>
<td valign="bottom" bgcolor=#FFAFAF><div>&eacute;l / ella / usted p<font color="#0A14C4"><strong>i</strong></font>de</div></td>

<td valign="bottom" bgcolor=#FFAFAF><div>ellos / ellas / ustedes p<font color="#0A14C4"><strong>i</strong></font>den</div></td>
<br>
</tr>
</table>

<br>
As before, note that not all the forms change.  The pattern <font color="#0A14C4"><strong>looks like a boot</strong></font>.



</div></td></tr>







